===Etymology===
From {{suffix|antinomian|ism}}, coined by {{w|Martin Luther}}, notably used in his ''Against the Antinomians'' (1539).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{context|Christianity}} a religious movement which believes that only the spiritual 'law of Faith' (Romans 3:27) is essential for salvation; and which is 'against' all other practical 'laws' being taught as being essential for salvation; and refering to them as legalism.
# {{context|Judaism}} opposition to the [[Torah]].

